nodes.title: Resolution note
widgets_values:
### Automatic scaling and resolution calculation The initial image will be scaled on optimized math targeting a WAN 2.2 VAE (div16) resolution. Aspect will be calculated automatically and the video resolution will be set to the nearest possible match with the megapixel count. | Stage | Target MP | Quality | Use case | |---:|---:|---:|---| | 1 | 0.25 | Preview
~ 360p| Motion/physics tests. | | 2 | 0.33 | Fast
~ 432p| Simple quality. | | 3 | 0.40 | SD Speed
~ 480p| "Sweet spot" for speed. | | 4 | 0.60 | SD
~ 576p| Optimal for mobile-first content. | | 5 | 0.72 | Balanced HD
~ 640p| Consistent, good details. | | 6 | 0.85 | HD
~ 720p| Very stable, crisp details. | | 7 | 1.05 | THD
~ 768p| Maximum stability for Image-to-Video. | | 8 | 1.15 | THD+
~ 800p| 16GB VRAM "sweet spot". | | 9 | 1.30 | HQ
~ 900p| High detail, very slow (Requires high VRAM). | | 10 | 2.07 | FHD
~ 1080p| Production grade detail, extreme slow (Requires very high VRAM). |

nodes.title: BASIC settings
widgets_values:
| Setting | Default / Example | Description | |--------:|------------------:|------------:| | **Seconds** | 5 | Set the desired length of the video in seconds. | | **CRF** | 20, webm, VP9 | Video compression level. Visually lossless. Set on VHS Node.| | **FPS** | 24 | Frames per second for videos. SVI works well with 24. | | **Shift** | 8 | Default 8. Adjust and test; WAN 2.2 SVI valid in range 8-12. | | **Steps total** | 6 | Total steps - node handles step math. More steps ‚Üí higher quality but longer generation. Use even numbers. | | **Step Refiner** | 3 | Default 2 (50% of 4). Change to test different swap behavior. | | **Sampler** | euler | "Euler" works everytime. Other samplers can enhance detail or motion. This has major impact on how the video is generated. | | **Scheduler** | simple | "Simple" works eveytime. Other like "beta" and others can enhance some samplers. | | **Seed** | number + fixed | Every stage has a fixed seed. Set a specific seed to reproduce the same outcome. | | **Sage Attention** | disabled | Can be enabled **if installed correctly** to speed-up video generation times. | | **Watermark upload** | none | Here you can upload a watermark image and calibrate the settings to your liking (subgraph). | | **Positive prompt** | none | Write your positive prompt!
1) Brief description of the setting/appearance
2) Actions, motions, story
3) Camera composition
CFG 1 normally disables/ignores the negative prompt! NAG effectively enables negative prompting on CFG 1.| | **Negative prompt** | none | Write what you would like to exclude. Works only if CFG > 1 or NAG is enabled | | **Checkpoints** | Safetensors/GGUf |Choose the type of Checkpoint to use. Wan 2.2 uses a different diffusion model for the first steps (high noise) vs the last steps (low noise). You can ether use safetensors or gguf.| | **CLIP** | standard encoder | Use your preferred standard CLIP text encoder. No CLIP Vision H ‚Äî not trained/implemented in WAN 2.2 and weights are disabled. | | **VAE** | same as WAN 2.1 | Still using the same VAE as WAN 2.1. |

nodes.title: Seconds and frames
widgets_values:
The optimal frame count is calculated automatically based on input seconds. | Seconds | 16 FPS frames
(Seconds*16)+1 | 24 FPS frames
(Seconds*24)+1 | Suggestion | |-------:|---------------------:|---------------:|---:| | 1 | 17 | 25 | | | 2 | 33 | 49 | | | 3 | 49 | 73 | | | 4 | 65 | 97 | | | 5 | 81 | 121 | native | | 6 | 97 | 145 | good for loop | | 7 | 113 | 169 | good for loop | | 8 | 129 | 193 | WAN starts looping back itself |

nodes.title: Features
widgets_values:
| Feature | Default / Example | Description |
|--------:|------------------:|------------:|
| **Color match** | off | This will try to match the color from the initial image to the samples. The color match algorithms default is set  by default to '0.75'. Feel free to test other strength. |
| **Interpolation** | off | This will interpolate your video to double fps at the end. Interpolated FPS = 2 √ó FPS. |
| **Upscale 2x (fast)** | off | Final resolution = 2 √ó start resolution while maintaining aspect ratio. No morph; color-correct fast lanczos upscale. Low VRAM consumption. |
| **Upscale /w Model (slow)** | off | Final resolution depends on the used upscaler model; Can change/enhance details and high VRAM consumption. |
| **Watermark** | off | Enable for a watermark overlay on video. |
| **SageAttention** | off | Needs to be installed! Possibly accelerates generation. |
| **FP16 accumulation** | on | Adds computational speed and memory efficiency |
This is needed to prevent OOM from very long videos for interpolation, upscaling or watermark.

nodes.title: Resolution and frame count (automated)
widgets_values:
Width & height settings must be divisible by 32 + 1.
Frame count must be divisible by 8 + 1.
